snippet: The driver of an oversize load that triggered an Interstate 5 bridge collapse May 23 said he had felt crowded by a passing vehicle, a preliminary report by the National Transportation Safety Board said.
abstract: Preliminary National Transportation Safety Board report says driver of oversize load that triggered Interstate 5 bridge collapse in Washington told investigators that he had felt crowded by passing vehicle and moved closer to side of bridge that had less clearance.
lead_paragraph: The driver of an oversize load that triggered an Interstate 5 bridge collapse May 23 said he had felt crowded by a passing vehicle, a preliminary report by the National Transportation Safety Board said.
